verbose_text: Moreover, the results showed that treatment with saturated hydrogen could significantly reduce renal function injury and inhibit the expression of inflammatory factors (i.e., TNF-alpha, IL-8, and IFN-gamma), as well as generation of the oxidative stress product, MDA; concurrently, this treatment could promote the expression of the anti-oxidative stress enzyme, SOD.
evidence: hydrogen could significantly reduce renal function injury
